sequenceDiagram
autonumber
actor User
participant App as Graph or History Webview
participant Router as Feature Message Router
participant Registry as RepositoryRegistry
participant UseCase as ForcePushWithLeaseUseCase
participant Repository as GitRepository
participant Worktree as Worktree
participant Plans as OperationPlanRegistry
participant Runtime as HybridGitRuntime
participant VscodeRuntime as VscodeGitRuntime
participant CliRuntime as CliGitRuntime

User->>App: Force push with lease
App->>Router: push request(repoLocator, worktreeLocator, branch)
Router->>Registry: resolve repository and worktree
Registry-->>Router: Repository and Worktree
Router->>UseCase: plan(repository, worktree, branch)
UseCase->>Repository: getUpstreamBranch(branch)
UseCase->>Repository: fetch(remote, { prune: true })
UseCase->>Repository: getAheadBehind(branch, upstream)
UseCase->>Plans: store high-risk remote plan with expected remote ref
Router-->>App: guarded operation plan
User->>App: Acknowledge lease preview
App->>Router: guarded acknowledgement(planId)
Router->>Plans: validate acknowledgement
alt Preview is stale
  Plans-->>Router: validation error
  Router-->>App: plan expired error
else Preview is current
  Router->>UseCase: execute(validated plan)
  UseCase->>Worktree: forcePushWithLease(remote, branch)
  Worktree->>Runtime: forcePushWithLease(context, input)
  alt VS Code runtime supports credentials
    Runtime->>VscodeRuntime: forcePushWithLease(context, input)
  else VS Code runtime cannot support context
    Runtime->>CliRuntime: forcePushWithLease(context, input)
  end
  Runtime-->>Worktree: success
  Router-->>App: operation success and refresh requested
end
